prompt: In section 94-85, what is special exception standards?
completion: special exception standards is City staff or the historic preservation board may grant special exceptions to some base dimensional standards as described in text below and summarized in Table III-3.

prompt: In section 94-85, what is wall height exception?
completion: wall height exception is The historic preservation board may grant a limited exception to the maximum wall height at the side setback for additions to contributing historic structures according to the table of special exception standards in subsection 94-85(a).

prompt: In section 94-85, what is site setback exception?
completion: site setback exception is The historic preservation board may grant a limited exception to the minimum side setback on one side of the property for additions to contributing historic structures according to the table of special exception standards in subsection 94-85(a). An exception shall not be granted where any portion of the resulting building, including encroachments such as roof eaves, would be located closer than two feet to an adjacent property line.

prompt: In section 94-85, what is lot coverage exception for one-story structures?
completion: lot coverage exception for one-story structures is City staff may grant a limited exception to the maximum lot coverage standard for all new construction and additions according to the table of special exception standards in subsection 94-85(a) where all structures on a property are one story.

prompt: In section 94-85, what is lot coverage and floor area exceptions for detached rear accessory structures?
completion: lot coverage and floor area exceptions for detached rear accessory structures is City staff may grant limited exceptions to the maximum lot coverage and floor area ratio standards for all new construction and additions according to the Table III-3.

prompt: In section 94-85, what is lot coverage and floor area ratio exceptions through special exception review?
completion: lot coverage and foor area ratio exceptions through special exception review is The historic preservation board may grant limited exceptions to the maximum lot coverage or floor area ratio standards for all new construction and additions according to the table of special exception standards in subsection 94-85(a). A special exception may be granted for either the lot coverage or floor area ratio standard, but not both. This does not apply to one-story structures where lot coverage and floor area ratio are the same.

prompt: In section 94-85, what is alternative minimum floor area for very small or constrained lots?
completion: alternative minimum foor area for very small or constrained lots is City staff may grant an exception to the floor area ratio standard where it would restrict the maximum buildable floor area to less than 1,700 square feet on a lot. In such cases a maximum floor area standard of 1,700 square feet may instead be used. Note that other dimensional standards such as minimum setbacks and maximum overall height standards may still restrict the maximum buildable floor area to less than 1,700 square feet.

prompt: In section 94-85, what is alternative garage location standards?
completion: alternative garage location standards is The historic preservation board may grant a limited exception to the garage location standard for additions to contributing historic structures according to the table of special exception standards in subsection 98-85(a).
